resources.string: A bottom app bar provides a docked bar at the bottom of the screen for common application actions. The bottom app bar includes a floating button for a primary action and a navigation bar area for secondary actions.

Bottom navigation bars make it easy to explore and switch between top-level views in a single tap. This navigational element resides at the bottom of the screen, and provides direct access for three to five destinations within an app.
